reviews.text:
I've visited twice now and tried a variety of different things, and all of them were wonderful!

The Chicago deep dish is more like just a thick crust pizza with sauce on top, but it was good. The hand stretched crust is my favorite - that perfect balance between just slightly crispy on bottom, with a soft, chewy outer crust.

I don't usually dip things in marinara, but I love theirs! I found myself dipping the toasted ravioli (delicious on their own!), the mozzarella sticks, and the outer crust of each piece of pizza. It's thick, full of flavor, and not overly sweet.

We had the same server both times and she was friendly and attentive, even though one of the times we were there every table was full, as well as some of the patio seating. They also seem to do quite a lot of carry out orders.
The best place I've ever had pizza, hands down. Friendly people, amazing food, all lead to a great dining experience!!

2024
I love the Henry pizza its my absolute favorite but the chicken bacon ranch, & Philly cheese steak pizza's are delicious too. Delivery drivers are always pleasant.

3-12-25
And today we got a free mystery pizza. Lol
We ordered teriyaki wings, bbq boneless wings, cheese garlic bread and fries.  Everything was delicious!

Excellent pizza!

They will also do half baked pizzas as well.

Worth the drive to Marthasville from Washmo for some excellent pizza.

I prefer the hand tossed over the Chicago style but the Chicago style was good too.

detailedReviews.text:
Solid food at a really reasonable price! Showed up still hot for delivery in Washington!

We were looking to try something new where we live in Washington. Pizza was on the brain and it came down to just a couple. Philly's had good looking pizzas in the photos. So, we crossed our fingers and hoped they would deliver from Marthasville. They did! PSA: tip your delivery drivers... especially if they have a 16 mile round trip so you don't have to get off your couch.. you pay the person for the luxury and convenience of delivery!

Highly recommend to try to switch things up!
